    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/en/">VeVolt</a><span>/</span><a href="/en/blog/">Blog</a></nav>
    <div class="article-intro"><div class="article-hero"><img src="/assets/screens/en-community-720.webp" width="1280" height="720" alt="VeVolt Community reports for an EV charging station" fetchpriority="high"></div><header class="article-header"><p class="eyebrow"><span class="signal"></span>VeVolt guide</p><h1>How to check whether an EV charger is working</h1><p class="lede">No single signal is perfect. The safest decision combines official operator information, recent community context and a backup location.</p><p class="article-meta">Updated 18/07/2026 · 8 min read</p></header></div>
    <div class="article-layout"><div class="article-body"><section><h2>Look for official status first</h2><p>When the operator provides a real-time app or support channel, use it to check connector status and access requirements before leaving.</p></section><section><h2>Read recent reports</h2><p>Recent reports can reveal a broken plug, occupied bay, blocked entrance or new tariff. Pay attention to the date and whether the report matches your connector.</p><ul><li>Operator status</li><li>Timestamp of reports</li><li>Matching connector</li><li>Venue opening hours</li><li>Compatible backup</li></ul></section><section><h2>Always keep a fallback</h2><p>For a low-battery arrival, identify another compatible charger before starting the route. A fallback turns uncertainty into a manageable detour.</p></section><section><h2>Frequently asked questions</h2><div class="faq-list"><details class="faq-item"><summary>Does a recent positive report guarantee success?</summary><p>No. Conditions can change between the report and your arrival.</p></details><details class="faq-item"><summary>What should I report after a failed attempt?</summary><p>Share the connector, time, visible error and access condition without exposing personal data.</p></details></div></section></div>
    <aside class="article-aside"><h2>Use VeVolt in your routine</h2><p>Find chargers, check reports, plan alternatives and record your experience in one app.</p><a class="button primary" href="/en/testers">Join the test</a><h2>Sources and further reading</h2><ul class="source-list"><li><a href="https://support.google.com/maps/answer/9773205?hl=pt-BR" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Maps - Built-in features for electric vehicles</a></li><li><a href="https://support.google.com/waze/answer/13259753?hl=pt-BR" rel="noopener noreferrer">Waze - Find charging stations along a route</a></li></ul></aside></div>
    <section class="section compact"><div class="section-heading"><div><p class="kicker">Related guides</p><h2>Keep learning</h2></div></div><div class="grid two"><article class="article-card"><div class="article-card-body"><h3>Can you own an electric car without a home charger?</h3><p>Assess public charging, workplace access, routine distance, charging time and cost before relying on an EV without home charging.</p><a class="text-link" href="/en/blog/electric-car-without-home-charger">Read article →</a></div></article><article class="article-card"><div class="article-card-body"><h3>EV charging at shopping centers, supermarkets and hotels</h3><p>Check access, parking, session activation, stay limits and etiquette when charging at a destination.</p><a class="text-link" href="/en/blog/how-to-use-ev-charging-at-shopping-centers-hotels">Read article →</a></div></article></div></section>
